  "prompt": "Why do girls wear sports bras?",
  "response": "Girls and women wear sports bras for several reasons:\n\n1. Support during physical activity\n- Reduce breast movement during exercise\n- Minimize discomfort and pain during sports or workouts\n- Prevent potential tissue damage from excessive bouncing\n\n2. Comfort\n- More comfortable than regular bras during exercise\n- Less restrictive and made of breathable materials\n- Designed to wick away sweat\n\n3. Protection\n- Reduce strain on breast tissue and ligaments\n- Help prevent long-term sagging\n- Provide stability during high-impact activities\n\n4. Performance\n- Allow for better range of motion\n- Help athletes feel more confident during physical activities\n\n5. Style\n- Often worn as casual or athletic wear\n- Can be considered a fashion item\n\nThe level of support varies depending on the type of sports bra and the intensity of the physical activity.",
